# Keep host-built artifacts out of the Docker build context. Without this,
# `COPY byh_app/backyardhero /app/byh_app/` in the Dockerfile clobbers the
# Linux-ABI node_modules that `npm ci` just built inside the image with the
# macOS Mach-O ones from the developer's laptop, which then crash at runtime
# with "invalid ELF header" on better_sqlite3.node and friends.

# Node / Next.js build outputs
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.swc
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/.pnpm-debug.log*

# Python
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/*.pyd
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/venv
**/.venv

# Local data + secrets that shouldn't bake into the image
data/
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
**/*.swp

# VCS
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
